channel.title: Help me with Webclient please!
channel.description:
Ok well i am using [url=http://google.com/runescape-development/google/downloads/299302-pi-hybrid-pvp-v2-508-maps-634-items-602-npcs-602-anims-gfx-more.html]this client and source[/url] and i am using [url=http://google.com/runescape-development/rs2-client/tutorials/300270-how-make-webclient-hybrid-pvp-v2-client-4.html] this webclient guide.[/url] I followed all the instructions in the webclient guide but i used [url=http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,501217.0/prev_next,prev.html#new] this webclient guide for web. com[/url]. Because i am using webs. com. I jarred perfectly and nothing went wrong. but i still seem to be getting this error when loading my webclient.
"Java Plug-in 1.6.0_29 Using JRE version 1.6.0_29-b11 Java HotSpot(TM) Client VM User home directory = C:\Users\Josh ---------------------------------------------------- c: clear console window f: finalize objects on finalization queue g: garbage collect h: display this help message l: dump classloader list m: print memory usage o: trigger logging q: hide console r: reload policy configuration s: dump system and deployment properties t: dump thread list v: dump thread stack x: clear classloader cache 0-5: set trace level to <n> ----------------------------------------------------
load: class client.class not found. java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: client.class at sun.plugin2.applet.Applet2ClassLoader.findClass(Unknown Source) at sun.plugin2.applet.Plugin2ClassLoader.loadClass0(Unknown Source) at sun.plugin2.applet.Plugin2ClassLoader.loadClass(Unknown Source) at sun.plugin2.applet.Plugin2ClassLoader.loadClass(Unknown Source) at java.lang.ClassLoader.loadClass(Unknown Source) at sun.plugin2.applet.Plugin2ClassLoader.loadCode(Unknown Source) at sun.plugin2.applet.Plugin2Manager.createApplet(Unknown Source) at sun.plugin2.applet.Plugin2Manager$AppletExecutionRunnable.run(Unknown Source) at java.lang.Thread.run(Unknown Source) Exception: java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: client.class"
And it looks like this: [IMG]http://i40.tinypic.com/vz7kec.png[/img]
If you need any other information just reply to this post with what you need. Also i dont know if this matters, but i am using this link in my cachedownloader.java. : http://uppit.com/ibfvmcgzgg6k/cache.zip

item.description:
@A_New_LIght wrote:

You are not directing it to read/manifest your client.class. If you have two separate folders in your client folder for class and java files then you have to direct it to the class folder then type client.
